snippet.textDisplay: I've owned several Subarus and not once had a head gasket failure.  If it was so bad, it wouldn't be made and or still popular. You're trying to compare a super massed produced engine, so failures will always look a lot higher based on the amount made. It's not even a hard or expensive repair for any hobbiest to do themselves anyway. I wouldn't pay $15,000 with that milage for other reasons such as body flex,  or worn seals and chipped underbody paint causing rust or beat up interior/silly electrical gremlins. With such an aftermarket for Subaru and so much parts sharing, there's a ton of support out there for anything mechanical (until you get into the Sti).
